Okay now I will start to define the High level aspect of the design
At first we can have Main class lets call it GameEngine it will be responsible for driving the entire scope of the game. It will be calling BoardService and MoveValidatorService
BoardService is responsible for tracking the board which is a 8*8 grid of pieces as any cell can contain a piece. Any operation like changing the position of a piece will be first validated via MoveValidatorService and then the corresponding piece can be placed on the relavant cell. Any move like attcking an opponent piece or giving a check happens in BoardService. if we are giving a check then it implies that only pieces that can protect the king can be moved or the king can move to a safer square. If at any position a player has no valid moves but the king is safe then the game ends in a draw and its called stalemate. If the king has no valid moves and is under check then the game ends with a victory for the player who gives the check.
Now lets discuss the MoveValidatorService is details
1) Pawn - we can have a variable in Piece (Will come later on piece) hasMoved this will tell us if the particular piece has moved or not. If moved then the pawn can only move 1 box forward for WHITE it will be bottom to up for BLACK it will be top to bottom. If any of our pawn is on 5th row and an enemy pawn directly comes next to our pawn in the same rank we can move in a diagonal direction to capture it enpassant and the pawn can only attack in one diagonal to the right or left like i+1 j+1 or i+1 or j-1
2) Lets quickly wrap other pieces like Knight which is only allowed to move in an L shape kinda like i+2, j+1 or i+2, j-1 or i+1, j+2 or i-1, j+2 and similarly for all 8 directions in an L shape
3) Bishop can move in diagonally like i+1 j+1 or i+2, j+2 or i-1, j-1
4) Rook can move in horizontal direction i+1, i+2, i+3 or j+1, j+2, j+3
5) Queen can move in all 8 direction which is a combination from Bishop and Rook.
6) King can only move in 8 direction but only 1 square around it. If King has not moved and no other piece is in the path between a rook and a king we can castle the king where king moves in more than 1 cell at a time and rook is placed right next to the king in appropriate direction.

Now there are few rules.
